2026-05-24 | Last Remaining Coin After Greedy Picks

	Question
Return value of final remaining coin.
	Key Insight
At every step:
		remove one end coin greedily.
So we can directly simulate the process
using two pointers.
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
		left = 0
		right = n-1
2.	While more than one coin remains:
		compare arr[left] and arr[right]
3.	Remove larger one:
		if left coin >= right coin:
				left++
		else:
				right--
4.	When left == right:
		that coin remains
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int lastCoin(vector<int>& arr) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = arr.size() - 1;
        while(left < right){
            if(arr[left] >= arr[right]){
                left++;
            }
            else{
                right--;
            }
        }
        return arr[left];
    }
};
	Key Insight
Since players always greedily remove
the larger end coin,
the process becomes a straightforward
two-pointer simulation.
